I see how having every option in a single document would be neat to search for all the settings in a single place without having to jump between READMEs, but I see how that it becomes really hard to maintain and read.

I also see the point of avoiding duplication by maintaining the settings in diff places.

I find it a bit difficult to find a common ground for these two scenarios, but I'm leaning towards separating settings by functionality, in this case I think the division by role that Beto is doing is a nice approach. Sorry I'm not giving great feedback here, just my 2¢.

Hi Tatiana! The change looks nice. I would like to ask you some questions, in any case:

- I guess you are missing to include submit_preflight_to_pyxis usage in the code to do some extra checks
- Are this kind of files (https://www.distributed-ci.io/files/ced6ac92-576b-46ef-9d6e-8412a7b210fc) the ones generated by Pyxis? If not, what is the result of submitting the results to Pyxis? Something to be seen in a GUI?

Patch Set 5:

Hi Ramon, thank you for the review!

> - I guess you are missing to include submit_preflight_to_pyxis usage in the code to do some extra checks

Ehm, I check it once at the entry point, in plays/tests.yml. It's like with the `do_cnf_cert` variable for the cnf-cert role.

> - Are this kind of files (https://www.distributed-ci.io/files/ced6ac92-576b-46ef-9d6e-8412a7b210fc) the ones generated by Pyxis? If not, what is the result of submitting the results to Pyxis? Something to be seen in a GUI?

These files are results of preflight tests, they are generated during the execution of the preflight role, here: https://github.com/redhat-cip/dci-openshift-app-agent/blob/master/roles/preflight/tasks/preflight_check_operator.yml#L81-L88 
The whole flow looks like this:
1/ DCI runs preflight cert suite and generates the results.json files
2/ Then, if `submit_preflight_to_pyxis` is defined to true, DCI takes these files, converts them into Pyxis's format templates/test_results.json.j2, and then submit them to Pyxis.
3/ The results of submission are displayed in the UI connect.redhat.com
